// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/parse/grammar/function-keyword/pass-func.test
//
// US1 / FR-016 / `S26` parser-equivalence fixture pair (T032a) — the
// `func` spelling. The companion `pass-function.test` fixture
// exercises the `function` spelling on otherwise-identical input;
// the two AST snapshots MUST share the same `NodeKind` names and
// the same nesting shape (`SourceRange` offsets differ by the
// keyword-length delta, which the directives below do NOT pin).
//
// Per `lang.ebnf §7`:
//   function_definition = ( "func" | "function" ) scoped_identifier
//                         action_statement ;
//
// and parser-note `S26`:
//   "func" ≡ "function". The Sema-time canonicalization warning
//   ("prefer `func`") is M3's responsibility — at M2 the parser
//   accepts either spelling and produces the same AST node kind
//   (`FuncDefn`).
//
// **Failing-state evidence (FR-029)**: against the unchanged tree at
// `7bc1aea`, the M1 driver does not implement `-emit=ast`. Invoking
// it exits with the "unknown emit stage" path (exit 2) and the
// FileCheck pipeline observes a mismatch. The test fails before
// the parser implementation lands.

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  func ready { }\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// Same node-kind sequence as the companion `pass-function.test`:
// `CompilationUnit` → `ModuleBlock` (named `m`) → `FuncDefn` (named
// `ready`) → an empty `ParallelBlock` body.

// CHECK:      (CompilationUnit
// CHECK:        (ModuleBlock
// CHECK-SAME:   name=m
// CHECK:          (FuncDefn
// CHECK:            (ParallelBlock
